The article discusses a letter from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Speaker of the House, in which he reports issuing an Executive Order to expand the national emergency declared in 2006 regarding Belarus. The order states that the Belarusian regime's actions, including suppressing democracy, human rights abuses, and disrupting international air travel, pose an unusual and extraordinary threat to the national security and foreign policy of the United States. The order enhances the sanctions designation criteria for current threats posed by the Belarusian regime. All executive departments and agencies are instructed to implement the order.